Frequently Asked Questions

Everything you need to know about Pagedone Tailwind CSS Components Library

Pagedone is open-source library of Tailwind CSS components, blocks, sections and pages designed to accelerate your web development workflow.

Everything in Pagedone Tailwind CSS Library is designed and developed for the latest version of Tailwind CSS, which is currently Tailwind CSS v4.1.

The components and templates in Pagedone Tailwind CSS Library are designed to work in the latest, stable releases of all major browsers, including Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge.

Using Pagedone Tailwind CSS Library is straightforward: browse our collection, find a component you need, copy the code, and paste it directly into your project.

Absolutely! Your license gives you permission to build as many of your own projects as you like, whether those are simple public websites or SaaS applications that end users need to pay to access.

As long as what you’re building isn’t a website builder or other tool that customers can use to create their own sites using elements that originate from Pagedone Tailwind CSS Library, you’re good to go.

Yes! As long as what you're building is some sort of actual website and not a derivative component library, theme builder, or other product where the primary purpose is clearly to repackage and redistribute our components, it's totally okay for that project to be open source.

No, you cannot use Pagedone Tailwind CSS Library to create derivative products like themes, UI kits, page builders, or anything else where you would be repackaging and redistributing our components or templates for someone else to use to build their own sites.
